### Tribune Publishing

The broader context of [Tribune Publishing](/Tribune_Publishing) is important, a sprawling media conglomerate that has seen its share of acquisitions and restructuring. The ownership by [Alden Global Capital](/Alden_Global_Capital) is a recent development, and one that has sparked considerable debate within the industry. Alden’s reputation for aggressive cost-cutting and a focus on profitability has led many to speculate about the future of these publications. The list of associated newspapers under the Tribune Publishing banner is extensive, a testament to a bygone era of media consolidation. From the venerable [Chicago Tribune](/Chicago_Tribune) to the more localized [Daily Southtown](/Daily_Southtown), and the various regional media groups like Daily Press Media Group and Hartford Courant Media, it paints a picture of a media empire in flux. Even the defunct entities like [Metromix](/Metromix) and [RedEye](/RedEye) serve as ghosts in the machine, reminders of past ambitions and changing tides. The inclusion of [El Sentinel](/El_Sentinel_(Orlando)) (defunct) under Orlando Sentinel Media Group is, again, a poignant footnote.

